        "**Explain the bias-variance tradeoff in the context of choosing the degree of the polynomial. What happens if the degree is too low or too high?**\n",
        "\n",
        "The bias-variance tradeoff refers to balancing model simplicity and flexibility. In polynomial regression, this depends on the degree of the polynomial.If the degree is too low, the model is too simple and cannot capture the data pattern, leading to high bias and underfitting.\n",
        "If the degree is too high, the model becomes too complex and fits noise in the data, leading to high variance and overfitting.\n",
