        "### 2) (3 points)\n",
        "**Why does Stochastic Gradient Descent have higher variance in parameter updates compared to Batch Gradient Descent? How does Mini-Batch GD try to balance this?**\n",
        "\n",
        "Stochastic Gradient Descent has higher variance because it updates the parameters using only one training example at a time. This makes each update noisy and sensitive to individual data points, causing fluctuations in the direction of the updates. Batch Gradient Descent uses the entire dataset for each update, which makes the gradient more stable and consistent, resulting in low variance but slower updates.\n",
        "Mini-Batch Gradient Descent balances both approaches by using a small subset of the data for each update. This reduces the noise compared to SGD while still being faster and more efficient than Batch Gradient Descent.\n"
      ]
