        "**Discuss the importance of feature scaling when using Gradient Descent for polynomial regression. What problems can arise without scaling?**\n",
        "\n",
        "Feature scaling is important in gradient descent because it ensures that all input features have similar ranges. In polynomial regression, higher-degree features can have very large values compared to lower-degree ones, which can make the optimization process unstable.Without scaling, gradient descent may converge very slowly or oscillate because the cost function becomes stretched in some directions. This can also lead to poor convergence or even divergence if the learning rate is not chosen carefully.\n",
